Abstract:
The cloud is all about elasticity on demand and cost savings, which is great. But it is also massively multi-tenanted and built with commodity hardware - which means it is prone to failure. Does this mean you can't use the cloud if you have many 9s in your SLA? Not necessarily. In this talk, Microsoft Azure MVP and seasoned Architect Mahesh Krishnan will talk about how you go about creating applications that run on the cloud that are resilient to failure, and what you - as an architect and developer - need to do to ensure that your application can absorb failure and be resilient.
&#160;
Mahesh will not only provide guidance on building fail-safe applications but show you an example of an application that keeps on working even in the event of a single DC wide outage - watch him as he takes one component after another offline while the app continues to work.
